originalText.text: This is a good place for self service and drop off wash and fold. The staff are helpful. The machines are new/clean and there is a change machine. It’s close and convenient. The prices are reasonable. However, delivery service has never come on time (or at all). Several times, I’ve had to call to remind them, they say it will come in 30-45 min and still doesn’t come. I end up waiting for hours and calling multiple times.

originalText.text: Super easy self-service with 2 different size washers and big dryers. I've never had trouble finding an open machine. They have a coin machine and can help you break change if needed. Place was bright and clean.

originalText.text: The people who run this laundromat are wonderful. They do their absolute best to take care of your clothes, even going so far as to pull something out for special handling when you’ve made the mistake of throwing it in with everything else. They are prompt and reliable. A true asset for those of us in the neighborhood who don’t have laundry in the building.

originalText.text: surprised by all the negative reviews as self-service here has been nothing but cheap & convenient for me! Vivian and the other women who work here have been nothing but kind and helpful - exchanging cash for coins, offering chairs, and even refunding me when I accidentally paid for the wrong dryer.

originalText.text: Horrible place, if you want to get yelled at for every move you make once you step in this place then feel free to come in. The woman that Is there makes the whole place uncomfortable to even do laundry. She stares and is so adamant for you to hurry up. She forces customers to use more machines than we should. Probably to make more money right? This place is insane, never seen such a horrific laundry Mat like this one before.
